  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Feasibility Study Time Together</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Time Together project is a feasibility study to ascertain if a time-credit system would help to support enterprising activity, community projects and local exchange in Siavonga. The problem: SNG has worked for many years with Women&apos;s Clubs across the Siavonga region to address issues of malnutrition and poverty. One of the challenges that they face is for very poor women trying to develop new enterprises to support their families and communities there is very little access to cash which has resulted in a limited means of exchange. As a result there are skills, talents, experience and abilities that are under-utilised in the community. The project: The feasibility study will explore the use of time credits to support non-monetary exchange - ie. volunteer time, goods and services and expertise. The Result: The feasbility study will enable SNG and Spice to co-design a new model of time banking that is cultural appropriate and best able to achieve its aims. By the end of the process we will have developed a full business plan for developing the time credits project with the SNG women&apos;s groups.</narrative>
  </description>
